    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD, featuring the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This chassis maintains its factory-spec 50/50 weight distribution and remains mechanically flawless with exceptional compression across all rotor faces. The five-speed manual gearbox offers crisp, short-throw engagement, paired with a Torsen limited-slip differential for optimal power delivery. Every vacuum line, bushing, and suspension component is in peak operational condition, preserving the tactile feedback of its four-wheel double-wishbone setup. This is a rare, unmolested example with original paint and a pristine interior, offering the visceral, high-revving performance that defines the Golden Era of Japanese sports cars.",
      "price": 48500.0,
